      • onReadBluetoothCommandSet

        public void onReadBluetoothCommandSet(int commandSet,
                                      byte status)
        Callback for request Blukii.readBluetoothCommandSet().

        The response value commandSet is a bitwise summary that determines the available Bluetooth requests.

        Use the following constants for detecting the available states:
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUETOOTH_INITIAL_ADVERTISING_INTERVAL
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUETOOTH_DELAYED_ADVERTISING_INTERVAL
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUETOOTH_ADVERTISING_UPDATE_DELAY
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUETOOTH_ADVERTISING_CHANNELS
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUETOOTH_DELAYED_CONNECTION_PARAMETER
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUETOOTH_CONNECTION_PARAMETER_DELAY
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUETOOTH_CURRENT_CONNECTION_PARAMETER
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUETOOTH_TXPOWER
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUETOOTH_LIMITED_ADVERTISING
        Parameters:
        commandSet - bitwise summary value for available requests concerning Bluetooth
        status - response status, can be one of the REQUEST_STATUS_... fields of class Blukii

      • onReadBlukiiCommandSet

        public void onReadBlukiiCommandSet(int commandSet,
                                   byte status)
        Callback for request Blukii.readBlukiiCommandSet().

        The response value commandSet is a bitwise summary that determines the available blukii settings requests.

        Use the following constants for detecting the available states:
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUKII_SYSTEM_COMMAND
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUKII_REBOOT_COUNTER
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUKII_RTC
        • Blukii.COMMANDSET_BLUKII_LED
        • SmartBeacon.COMMANDSET_BLUKII_IBEACON_ADVERTISING
        • SmartBeacon.COMMANDSET_BLUKII_EDDYSTONE_UID
        • SmartBeacon.COMMANDSET_BLUKII_SMARTBEACON
        Parameters:
        commandSet - bitwise summary value for available requests concerning blukii settings
        status - response status, can be one of the REQUEST_STATUS_... fields of class Blukii

      • onReadDeviceFirmware

        public void onReadDeviceFirmware(java.lang.String firmware,
                                 byte status)
        Callback for request Blukii.readDeviceFirmware().

        With the help of reading the firmware you can identify the blukii type. The scheme is XXX.YYY where XXX is the beacon type number and YYY is the version.

        • 001.YYY: SmartKey
        • 002.YYY: SmartBeacon type "Eddystone" (incl. iBeacon)
        • 003.YYY: SmartBeacon type "InfoBeacon" (incl. iBeacon)
        • 004.YYY: SmartSensor
        Parameters:
        firmware - firmware number string
        status - response status, can be one of the REQUEST_STATUS_... fields of class Blukii
